---
const concepts = [
  {
    title: 'Ontology contract',
    body: 'The schema-like object that tells SEOCHO which entities, relationships, and properties are valid.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Graph memory',
    body: 'The persisted graph facts, provenance, constraints, and evidence used by later agent questions.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Semantic query',
    body: 'A guarded retrieval path that uses ontology and graph context before answer synthesis.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Runtime surface',
    body: 'The HTTP layer for apps, agents, policy checks, traces, and shared graph access.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Run spec',
    body: 'A YAML file that makes ontology, documents, questions, models, and sweeps repeatable.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Evidence trail',
    body: 'Artifacts and traces that show what SEOCHO extracted, queried, repaired, or skipped.',
  },
];
---

<section class="w-full border-b border-white/10 bg-[#070707]">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 py-20 md:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.7fr_1.3fr] lg:items-start">
      <div>
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase text-amber-200/80">Read the project as concepts</p>
        <h2 class="seocho-display text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-white md:text-5xl">
          The vocabulary is the map.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 max-w-xl text-base leading-7 text-zinc-400">
          SEOCHO becomes much easier once you stop reading it as a pile of files
          and start reading it as a small set of moving parts.
        </p>
        <a href="/learn/" class="mt-7 inline-flex rounded-lg border border-white/15 px-4 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100 transition-colors hover:bg-white/10">
          Open concept guide
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3">
        {concepts.map((concept) => (
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-black/35 p-5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">{concept.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400">{concept.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
